Display of some standard information in the ModeLine is governed by these minor modes (toggles):

* `display-time-mode' -- Show/hide the current time.
* `line-number-mode' -- Show/hide the current line number.
* `column-number-mode' -- Show/hide the current column number.
* `size-indication-mode' (>= Emacs 22) -- Show/hide the current buffer size.
* `display-battery-mode' (>= Emacs 22) -- Show/hide laptop battery information. Supported: GNU/Linux APM, ACPI, and Mac OS X 10.3.x (see JerameyCrawford),  FreeBSD and OpenBSD (see JoelHolveck).

Here are particular enhancements to the mode-line:

* ModeLineMinorModeMenu -- Pop up minor-mode menus from the mode-line.
* ModeLinePosition -- Show region size if region is active (in TransientMarkMode). Highlight column number, if greater than `modelinepos-column-limit' (user option).  
* ModeLinePosAtBeginning -- Put line and column numbers at beginning of mode-line, so they are visible even when the TextCursor is inside a function with a long name.
* HideModeLine -- Hide the mode-line, to save screen real estate.
* LunarModeLine -- Display current lunar phase in the modeline.
* ModeLineDirtrack -- show the buffer's current directory in the mode-line.
* SmlModeLine -- Indicate in the mode-line, in a scrollbar-like way, the portion of the buffer that is visible in the window.

How to customize the mode-line further:

* http://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/elisp/html_node/Mode-Line-Format.html

